TOPOSES IN COMO
Call for participation

School: 24-26 June 2018 - Conference: 27-29 June 2018=20
Lake Como School of Advanced Studies and Universit=C3=A0 degli Studi =
dell=E2=80=99Insubria=20
http://tcsc.lakecomoschool.org =20

* Scope *
------------

The event =E2=80=9CToposes in Como=E2=80=9D, which represents the second =
edition of the conference =E2=80=9CTopos =C3=A0 l=E2=80=99IHES=E2=80=9D =
held in France in 2015, will consist of a three-day school, offering =
introductory courses for the benefit of students and mathematicians who =
are not already familiar with topos theory, followed by a three-day =
conference featuring both invited and contributed presentations on new =
theoretical advances in the subject as well as applications of toposes =
in different fields such as algebra, topology, number theory, algebraic =
geometry, logic, homotopy theory, functional analysis and computer =
science.

* School lecturers *
--------------------------

Francis BORCEUX (Universit=C3=A9 Catholique de Louvain)
Olivia CARAMELLO (Universit=C3=A0 degli Studi dell=E2=80=99Insubria - =
Como)
Alain CONNES (IHES)
Laurent LAFFORGUE (IHES)

* Conference invited speakers *
------------------------------------------

Tibor BEKE (University of Massachusetts)
Ingo BLECHSCHMIDT (University of Augsburg)
Eduardo DUBUC (University of Buenos Aires)
Pieter HOFSTRA (University of Ottawa)
Maria Emilia MAIETTI (Universit=C3=A0 degli Studi di Padova)
Andrew PITTS (University of Cambridge)
Mauro PORTA (Universit=C3=A9 de Strasbourg)
Bas SPITTERS (Aarhus University)
David SPIVAK (MIT)

